</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Charles Schwab Corp.: Profit at America's largest discount broker more than 
doubled in 1989 to $19 million. Revenue totaled $553.2 million, up 41% from 
1988. The San Francisco firm cited a 24% gain in commission revenue due to 
stronger market activity and increased interest revenue. 
</P>
</TEXT>
