<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
California Federal Bank said Edward E. Wendt was elected executive vice 
president, administration. 
</P>
<P>
Wendt joined California Federal in 1976 as head of the bank's savings systems 
department. In 1987, he was elected to the position of senior vice president, 
responsible for information services. In 1989, he was given additional 
responsibilities, including loan services, administrative services and property 
management. He continues to manage these functions under his new title. 
</P>
</TEXT>
