<HEADLINE>
<P>
MORNING REPORT: WEDDING BELLS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BETH KLEID , Arts and entertainment reports from The Times, national and 
international news services and the nation's press. 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Roseanne to Tie the Knot?: Less than a month after announcing her wedding plans 
were off, Roseanne Barr was spotted Wednesday taking out a marriage license at 
the Santa Monica Superior Court, although her publicist said Wednesday that 
Barr has not yet married. "I can't believe I'm doing this," Barr was overheard 
saying as she walked in the door to the courthouse. 
</P>
<P>
Barr will marry her long-time friend and collaborator Tom Arnold, but no 
wedding date has been set, said Barr's publicist Alana Rothstein. "She's still 
literally taking it day by day," Rothstein said. In December, Barr called off 
her Jan. 20 wedding with Arnold, explaining in a statement that he was in an 
alcohol and drug rehabilitation clinic. Barr's divorce from husband Tom 
Pentland was scheduled to become finalized Wednesday. BETH KLEID 
</P>
</TEXT>
<GRAPHIC>
<P>
Photo, Tom Arnold and Roseanne Barr 
</P>
</GRAPHIC>
