<HEADLINE>
<P>
WESTSIDE DIGEST: WEST HOLLYWOOD; 
</P>
<P>
5 NAMED TO SAFETY PANEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council has appointed five members to the newly created Public Safety 
Commission. 
</P>
<P>
The commission was established last fall partially in response to frequent 
complaints that local sheriff's deputies had engaged in anti-gay behavior. 
Besides serving as a forum for citizen comments on law-enforcement issues, the 
panel will also deal with fire prevention and disaster preparedness. 
</P>
<P>
The new members of the panel are: Christopher L. Fairchild, Aslan Brooke, Norma 
Kemper, Bronwen McGarva and John Altschul. 
</P>
<P>
Nancy Greenstein, assistant to the city manager, said that the panel will 
probably meet once a month but that no official guidelines for its operation 
have been adopted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
