<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY DIGEST: BELLFLOWER; 
</P>
<P>
HOME ECONOMICS TEACHER GETS AWARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A home economics teacher at Bellflower High School was one of two teachers 
selected statewide for the 1989 Home Economics Teachers Recognition Award. 
</P>
<P>
Joyce Grohmann, who has been teaching at Bellflower High School since 1984, was 
given the award for her dedication and commitment. 
</P>
<P>
Three years ago, Grohmann was awarded a $25,000 federal grant to set up a 
catering class at the high school. She said her students operated a small 
restaurant and catered meals to the faculty and the community. 
</P>
<P>
"The kids learned from the classroom how to run a catering business," she said. 
</P>
<P>
Grohmann also has been active in Future Homemakers of America. She attended 
Cypress College and received her bachelor's degree from Cal State Long Beach in 
1980. 
