<P>
SOUTH BAY DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: GUNMAN IN CAR KILLS BICYCLIST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 19-year-old Inglewood man was shot to death Sunday night by a gunman in a 
passing vehicle as he rode his bicycle along a residential street, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Jesus Alberto Montes was shot about 9:15 p.m. in the 3800 block of West 105th 
Street as he pulled up alongside a Datsun carrying four men in their early 20s, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
After the car sped off, Montes struggled to his feet, police said. However, the 
car returned and a passenger shot him again, this time hitting him in the 
heart, police said. 
</P>
<P>
Police said Montes collapsed near a home and was pronounced dead at Daniel 
Freeman Memorial Hospital. Investigators said they had no motive for the 
shooting, although they believe the four men knew Montes. 
</P>
