<HEADLINE>
<P>
HIGH SCHOOL BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
MT. CARMEL NEARS RECORD WITH 132 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mt. Carmel came within four points of tying the section record for most points 
scored in a game by a boys' basketball team when it defeated Orange Glen, 
132-58, at home Wednesday night. 
</P>
<P>
Sweetwater holds the record, 136 in a 1988 victory over Coronado (48). Mt. 
Carmel passed the 130 scored by Sweetwater in a victory over Montgomery (51) in 
1981. 
</P>
<P>
The previous high for Mt. Carmel was 116 in 1979 against El Camino. 
</P>
<P>
Seven players for Mt. Carmel had season highs and eight were in double figures. 
</P>
<P>
Those in double figures were: Tom LaBuda, 23, Shane Knight, 17, Ryan Wootton, 
17, Bill Landry, 16, Jason Beeman, 16, Mike Graves, 16, Matt Castillo, 12 and 
Jon Young, 11. 
</P>
<P>
Mt. Carmel improved to 13-3, 5-0 in Palomar League play, and Orange Glen fell 
to 0-12, 0-5. 
</P>
<P>
In other Palomar League games: 
</P>
