<P>
MEETING ON TRASH SCHEDULED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council has scheduled a meeting for Tuesday between city officials and 
representatives of Best Disposal Co. and its prospective buyer, National 
Environmental Waste Management Corp., to review terms of the planned takeover. 
</P>
<P>
Riverside-based National would assume Best's contract to provide trash pickup 
services to the city. But a final date for the sale has not yet been set, 
because National is awaiting completion of an environmental report on Best's 
Monrovia site. The report is expected within a month. 
</P>
