<P>
REFINANCING NETS $2 MILLION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The city's Redevelopment Agency refinanced three redevelopment projects, 
generating $2.3 million, part of which will pay back a city loan. 
</P>
<P>
The $300,000 loan was made last month, when the agency was not able to meet 
obligations for the San Gabriel River, Puente-Merced and Central Business 
District redevelopment areas. 
</P>
<P>
"The agency is now in a position to meet all its obligations," said Mayor Pro 
Tem Bette Lowes. 
