<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: MONROVIA; 
</P>
<P>
FARMERS' MARKET POSSIBLE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The city may soon have a farmers' market, if downtown merchants agree to 
support the market financially. 
</P>
<P>
The City Council on Tuesday approved the concept of a market upon the 
recommendation of the Planning Commission and the Community Services 
Commission. A possible site might be the north side of Lime Avenue, west of 
Myrtle Avenue. 
</P>
<P>
The city will seek sponsors among members of the Downtown Monrovia Merchants 
Assn. to come up with the nearly $12,700 needed to cover publicity, insurance, 
licensing and management expenses for the first year. 
</P>
<P>
Mayor Pro Tem Mary Wilcox said the market could begin as early as March 1, in 
time for strawberry season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
