SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: COVINA; 
</P>
<P>
PLANNING, ZONING FEES SET 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council approved five new fees for city planning and zoning services 
Monday, including a landscape inspection fee that will cost developers $650 or 
more per project. 
</P>
<P>
The city will now charge $1,100 for zoning ordinance amendments, $450 for minor 
amendments to subdivision maps, $350 for changes to planned community 
development proposals and $65 for some transfers of alcoholic beverage 
licenses. 
</P>
<P>
Previously, there had been no charge for the services. 
</P>
