<P>
NEW WATER BOARD MEMBER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
John E. Maulding of Hacienda Heights has been selected to the 51-member board 
of the Metropolitan Water District of Southern California, which covers the six 
counties of Southern California. 
</P>
<P>
Maulding, a former board member of the Upper San Gabriel Valley Municipal Water 
District, is senior vice president of Willdan Associates, a civil engineering 
and planning firm based in Industry. 
</P>
<P>
One of two Upper San Gabriel Valley representatives to serve on the 
Metropolitan board, Maulding replaces Howard Hawkins of Covina, who retired 
after 25 years. Maulding was sworn in last week. 
