<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN GABRIEL VALLEY DIGEST: SOUTH PASADENA; 
</P>
<P>
ELECTRIC POWER RESTORED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Electric power was restored to the city's Police and Fire departments on 
Tuesday after a three-day outage. Rainwater from the weekend storm had leaked 
into an electrical panel in the basement of city offices last Saturday and 
contributed to an extensive internal power failure, City Manager John Bernardi 
said. 
</P>
<P>
For nearly 30 minutes on Saturday night, calls to the city's 911 emergency 
phone number were automatically transferred to the San Marino Police 
Department, Bernardi said. The Fire Department used generators and the Police 
Department drew its power from extension cords connected to City Hall 
administrative offices next door. 
</P>
<P>
"We're not really sure what happened at this point," Bernardi said, adding that 
the failure in the electrical system, installed when City Hall was built on 
Mission Street more than three years ago, is being investigated. 
</P>
<P>
It took until Tuesday to make the repairs because crews were unable to obtain 
needed parts during the Martin Luther King Jr. holiday weekend, Bernardi said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
