<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: ATHLETIC FOUNDATION AWARDS $748,000 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The foundation charged with disbursing surplus funds from the 1984 Olympics to 
groups that serve Southern California youths has approved grants and programs 
totaling $748,000 for the winter quarter, bringing to $27 million the total 
given out during the last five years. 
</P>
<P>
The largest grant, announced this week by the Amateur Athletic Foundation of 
Los Angeles, was the $150,000 gift to the Salesian Boys and Girls Club of Los 
Angeles, serving Eastside communities, for repair and renovation of its 
gymnasium. 
</P>
<P>
California Special Olympics Inc. received $148,600 for community sports 
training centers in Los Angeles, Pomona, Idyllwild, Orange County and the San 
Fernando Valley. 
</P>
<P>
Youth sports groups may apply for grants at the foundation headquarters at 2141 
W. Adams Blvd. in Los Angeles. 
</P>
