<HEADLINE>
<P>
NFL PLAYER'S TRANSITION GAME UNIQUE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
MURFREESBORO, Tenn. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Kenny Tippins of the Dallas Cowboys is among four football players who have 
joined the suspension-riddled and injury-depleted basketball team at Middle 
Tennessee State University. 
</P>
<P>
Tippins, who was on the Cowboys' developmental squad last fall, is back in 
school this semester to complete his degree. 
</P>
<P>
He is eligible to play basketball under NCAA rules because he was never 
redshirted as a college football player at the school. 
</P>
<P>
"I still can't believe all this is really happening," he said. "This is like 
something you hear about happening in the 1950s or '60s." 
</P>
<P>
Middle Tennessee Coach Bruce Stewart pieced together the makeshift team this 
week after eight players were suspended by the Ohio Valley Conference for 
fighting during a game against Tennessee Tech a week ago. 
</P>
<P>
Two other Blue Raider basketball players are injured. 
</P>
