<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE BASKETBALL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TONIGHT'S GAMES 
</P>
<P>
PACIFIC 10 CONFERENCE 
</P>
<P>
NO. 16 UCLA (11-2, 5-0) at STANFORD (10-3, 2-2), 8:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
TV -- ESPN. Radio -- KMPC (710). 
</P>
<P>
UCLA, a 73-67 winner over Arizona last Saturday, hopes to keep its perfect 
conference record intact against a Cardinal team that has won 19 of its last 20 
home games. Stanford is led by forward Adam Keefe, a 6-9, 230-pound sophomore 
from Irvine who is the Pac-10's No. 2 scorer and No. 1 rebounder, averaging 21 
points and 10.5 rebounds a game. Forward Andrew Vlahov, who is averaging 9.6 
points and 5.7 rebounds, is the only returning starter from a team that was 
26-7 last season, including two victories over UCLA. The Cardinal won its first 
eight games but has since lost to No. 1-ranked Kansas and to Oregon State and 
Washington in Pac-10 play. 
</P>
<P>
USC (6-6, 1-4) at CALIFORNIA (12-4, 3-2), 7:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
TV -- None. Radio -- KNX (1070). 
</P>
<P>
Tonight's game matches two of the top freshmen in the Pac-10, USC guard Harold 
Miner and Cal center Brian Hendrick. Miner has averaged 23.3 points in his last 
six games. Hendrick, a 6-foot-8 redshirt freshman from Diamond Bar High, is 
averaging 15.4 points and 7.9 rebounds. He led the NCAA in field goal 
percentage last week with 70.5%. Cal's three-guard offense has been effective. 
Point guard Keith Smith is averaging 16.5 points and 7.4 assists, and backcourt 
mate Ryan Drew is averaging 10.6 points. Forward Roy Fisher has also played 
well, averaging 15.1 points and 6.1 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
BIG WEST CONFERENCE 
</P>
<P>
CS FULLERTON (8-6, 2-3) at CS LONG BEACH (11-3, 4-2), 7:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
TV -- SportsChannel. Radio -- KORG (1190). 
</P>
<P>
Cal State Long Beach has won five of its last six games and is 6-0 in its 
campus gym. Rebounding from a defeat at UC Santa Barbara, the 49ers defeated 
first-place New Mexico State, 72-56, Monday night as guard Tyrone Mitchell had 
11 points, 11 rebounds, 11 assists and four steals. Forward Kevin Cutler had 
his best game in a month, scoring 17 points against the Aggies. Cal State 
Fullerton, which lost, 66-60, at San Jose State Monday night, is 2-6 on the 
road. Forward Cedric Ceballos is averaging 21.6 points a game, and guard Mark 
Hill is averaging 20.9. The teams have split their last four games. 
</P>
<P>
UC IRVINE (2-13, 0-6) at NEVADA LAS VEGAS (11-3, 5-1), 8 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
TV -- Channel 56. Radio -- KORG (1190). 
</P>
<P>
A loss tonight would clinch Irvine's second consecutive losing season and only 
the third in Coach Bill Mulligan's 10 seasons. Irvine has not won since 
defeating San Diego State, 75-62, on Dec. 16, a streak of eight losses. UNLV, 
the nation's ninth-ranked team, is tied for the conference lead with New Mexico 
State. Irvine is in last place. UNLV returns home after four road games, 
including victories at Temple on Saturday and Fresno State on Monday. An NCAA 
investigation into an unpaid school loan sidelined guard Anderson Hunt, the 
Rebels' third-leading scorer, for the Temple game. But Hunt, who averages 15.1 
points, returned against Fresno State. Forward Larry Johnson leads the Rebels, 
averaging 20.6 points and 10.7 rebounds. Center Ricky Butler averages 15.1 
points to lead Irvine. 
</P>
