<P>
Jack Morris, the winningest pitcher of the 1980s, agreed to a $2.1-million 
contract with a $2.1-million option for 1991 with the Detroit Tigers. But, in 
an unusual twist, the option is his and not the club's. 
</P>
<P>
Morris' agent, Richard Moss, believes Morris is only the third player in 
baseball history to get options -- the others were Robin Yount and Carney 
Lansford. 
