ORANGE COUNTY NEWSWATCH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Mark I. Pinsky and Steve Emmons 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PLOT THICKENS: Rep. Barbara Boxer (D-San Francisco) is lining up a meeting with 
Orange County Democrats in connection with her expected challenge to Sen. Alan 
Cranston in 1992. . . . She seeks "key people who would be interested in 
supporting me." . . . Cranston, weakened by his ties to Irvine-based Lincoln 
Savings &amp; Loan, has lashed back, calling one critic "a publicity-hungry 
political hack." (A3) Mark I. Pinsky and Steve Emmons 
</P>
