<P>
8% PAY HIKE OKD FOR CITY ADMINISTRATORS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The City Council approved pay raises for top administrators, increasing 
compensation by an average of 8%. 
</P>
<P>
Pay and benefits for the 13 department heads and other executives were 
increased retroactively to Oct. 28, when the union-represented employees 
received pay raises. 
</P>
<P>
City Manager William C. Winter will receive $130,238 a year in pay and 
benefits; Assistant City Manager Hugh Berry, who also is the director of 
engineering and community development, $122,385; City Atty. R.K. (Kerry) Fox, 
$106,125; Police Chief Philip A. Goehring, $112,056; Fire Chief Ron Coleman, 
$110,044; Finance Director Barbara Henderson, $98,885; and Development Services 
Director Paul Dudley, $96,691. 
</P>
<P>
The amounts include base pay and retirement premiums, insurance contributions 
and other reimbursements. 
</P>
<P>
The pay increases will cost the city about $63,000 more for the remaining six 
months of the fiscal year. 
</P>
