<HEADLINE>
<P>
BOYS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
LOS ALAMITOS WINS ON LATE FREE THROW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Anthony Napolitano made the second of two free throws with three seconds left 
give Los Alamitos High School a 58-57 victory over El Dorado in an Empire 
League basketball game Wednesday at El Dorado. 
</P>
<P>
The Golden Hawks (11-7 overall, 2-2 in the league) had a chance to win the 
game, but a shot Jerome Facione bounced off the rim at the buzzer. 
</P>
<P>
Mike Wilson scored 19 points and Dan Stockwell added 11 for Los Alamitos (14-6, 
4-0). Mike Bradach had 16 and Facione 14 for El Dorado. 
</P>
<P>
Loara 74, Cypress 72 -- Tes Whitlock scored 20 points to lead Loara (13-3, 2-2) 
at Cypress. Jared Rice scored 31 points for Cypress (7-11, 0-4). 
</P>
