<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY COLLEGE BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
LONG SHOTS SPARK RANCHO SANTIAGO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By STEVE KRESAL, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sophomore Gene Altamirano scored 22 points, including six three-point baskets, 
to lead Rancho Santiago College to an 87-67 victory over Fullerton in an Orange 
Empire Conference men's basketball game Wednesday at Rancho Santiago. 
</P>
<P>
Altamirano, a 6-foot-4 guard from Los Amigos High School, scored three of his 
three-pointers and had 11 points in each half. 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton took a 13-9 lead on a layup by Mike Keith with 14:12 left in the 
first half. After that, it was pretty much all Rancho Santiago. 
</P>
<P>
The Dons went on a 18-0 run in the next five minutes and led, 27-13, after a 
three-pointer by Mike Hunter. Rancho Santiago led, 41-26, at the half and 
Fullerton never got closer than 14 points the rest of the way. 
</P>
<P>
"I thought we played pretty well tonight," Rancho Santiago Coach Dana Pagett 
said. "We had some good spurts in there." 
</P>
<P>
Alvin Loftis scored 16, Matt Lien 14 and Corie Blount had 10 for Rancho 
Santiago. 
</P>
<P>
Altamirano was seven of 10 from the field overall, including six of seven on 
three-point attempts, and also led the Dons with six rebounds. He has made 57% 
(64 of 112) of his three-point attempts this season. 
</P>
<P>
Rashone Lewis scored 20 and Keith 13 for Fullerton (9-13, 0-4). Lewis led 
Fullerton with nine rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Santiago (21-1 overall and 4-0 in conference play) moves into a 
first-place tie with Cypress (18-3, 4-0) which was idle Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Santiago plays at Orange Coast Saturday, and Cypress will play at 
Riverside. Rancho Santiago, ranked second in the state, plays at sixth-ranked 
Cypress next Wednesday. 
</P>
<P>
In other Orange Empire Conference men's games: 
</P>
<P>
Golden West 95, Saddleback 86 -- Visiting Golden West broke open a close game 
with a 23-8 run midway through the second half. Saddleback led, 39-38, at the 
half, but Golden West took a 57-55 lead with 10:54 left in the game. 
</P>
<P>
From there, Golden West started its run and led, 80-63, seven minutes later. 
</P>
<P>
Sophomores Craig Rice and J.J Jenkins sparked the run for Golden West (16-8, 
3-2). Rice, a guard, scored eight consecutive points and Jenkins, a forward, 
added seven points. 
</P>
<P>
Jenkins led Golden West with 22 points and 10 rebounds. Ric Van Scoyce added 21 
and eight assists, Rice had 18 points, Jason Vaughan had 12 and Kevin Andersen 
10. 
</P>
<P>
Charles Lockard had 16 points, Bill Schellenberg 15, Terrell Malone 14, and 
Greg Reynolds and Matt Thompson 12 each for Saddleback (7-14, 0-4). 
</P>
<P>
Riverside 67, Orange Coast 37 -- Orange Coast turned the ball over a 
season-high 26 times and scored a season low 37 points in the loss at home. 
OCC, which dropped to 12-7 and 1-3, shot 33% (13 of 39) for the game. 
</P>
<P>
Paul Kos was the only OCC scorer in double figures with 12. Deon Robinson 
scored 13 points to lead Riverside (14-10, 3-2), which made half of its 54 
shots from the floor. 
</P>
<P>
In Orange Empire Conference women's basketball: 
</P>
<P>
Golden West 95, Saddleback 42 -- Sophomore forward Donna Gondringer scored 23 
points and had 14 rebounds to lead first-place Golden West (24-1, 5-0) at home. 
Stacee Johnson added 17 points and 14 rebounds for Golden West. Bits Sirchia 
had 10 points for Golden West, which led, 43-21, at the half. Saddleback is 
11-10, 2-2. 
</P>
<P>
Orange Coast 71, Riverside 65 -- Cindy Kollar scored 18 points and Kami Bigler 
added 14 for visiting Orange Coast (19-4, 3-1). 
</P>
<P>
Fullerton 77, Rancho Santiago 42 -- Angie Nelsen had 16 points and 12 rebounds 
to lead Fullerton (11-10, 3-1), and Gina Krouse had 15 points. Charisse Simon 
had 16 points for Rancho Santiago (5-11, 0-4). 
</P>
</TEXT>
