GIRLS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
LA QUINTA GAINS 46TH CONSECUTIVE LEAGUE VICTORY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The La Quinta High School girls' basketball team keeps rolling. Paced by senior 
center Amy Jalewalia's 33 points and seven rebounds, La Quinta defeated 
visiting Los Amigos, 64-30, Wednesday for its 46th consecutive victory in 
Garden Grove League play. 
</P>
<P>
La Quinta, which improved to 15-2 overall and 6-0 in league play, also was 
sparked by Heather Brannan, who had 11 points, 12 rebounds and five assists. 
</P>
<P>
Los Amigos was led by Carrie Elsaesser, who had 12 points, 16 rebounds and 
seven blocked shots. 
</P>
<P>
In other Garden Grove League games: 
</P>
<P>
Kennedy 71, Garden Grove 64 -- Senior guard Michelle Harris had 30 points and 
seven steals and junior guard Valerie Ruiz had 18 points, four assists and four 
steals to lead host Kennedy (8-8, 4-2). Freshman forward Lynly Matsumoto had 12 
points and 11 rebounds for Kennedy and Melanie Dear had 27 points for Garden 
Grove. 
</P>
<P>
Rancho Alamitos 49, Pacifica 30 -- Jenny Newsome scored 15 points and Marlene 
Rodriguez 14 to lead host Rancho Alamitos (10-2, 5-1). 
</P>
<P>
Santiago 37, Bolsa Grande 32 -- Becky Elcock had 17 points and Pricilla Demuth 
had 13 to lead Santiago (5-10, 2-5) at home. 
</P>
