</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Water supply -- A story in the Jan. 14 South Bay Edition said incorrectly that 
most of the South Bay's drinking water is drawn from local aquifers. According 
to the West Basin Municipal Water District, wells provide about a quarter of 
the South Bay's drinking water. The rest is drawn from water supplies diverted 
to the Los Angeles area from Northern California and the Colorado River. 
</P>
</TEXT>
