<P>
LOTTERY SWEETENS THE POT, ADDS $10 MILLION FOR SATURDAY'S DRAW 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SACRAMENTO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A surprise bonus prize will push Saturday's jackpot in the California Lottery's 
Lotto 6-49 game to a guaranteed $30 million, lottery officials said today. 
</P>
<P>
"This is the new decade kickoff -- off with a bang," said lottery spokeswoman 
Joanne McNabb. 
</P>
<P>
No one correctly guessed all six numbers in Wednesday's drawing, leaving the 
$7.6-million grand prize unclaimed. Typically, the jackpot in the next drawing 
would have jumped to about $15 million. 
</P>
<P>
Lottery officials announced earlier this month that they would augment the 
grand prize by $10 million some time in January. 
</P>
<P>
"This is it," McNabb said. "This is a surprise. . . . This is the first time 
we've had a special lotto jackpot bonus. It may not be the last." 
</P>
<P>
Lottery statisticians expect increased sales to boost the jackpot another $5 
million to the $30-million total. 
</P>
</TEXT>
