<P>
CHRYSLER TO IDLE 2,250 WORKERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
DETROIT 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Chrysler Corp. said today it will indefinitely idle more than 2,250 hourly and 
salaried workers at three U.S. assembly plants in late March as it slows down 
vehicle production. 
</P>
<P>
Company spokesman Doug Nicoll said 724 workers will be let go at Chrysler's 
Jeep plant in Toledo, Ohio, and 780 workers will be idled at its mid-sized car 
plant in Newark, Del. Another 750 workers will be indefinitely idled at its 
full-sized car plant in Belvidere, Ill., Nicoll said. 
</P>
<P>
All three plants will be closed the week of March 19. When they resume 
operations March 26, Chrysler will begin the process of reducing the work force 
at those plants. 
</P>
