<P>
TRUMP TO SELL YACHT FOR BIGGER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LONDON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Captain of capitalism Donald J. Trump is selling his sleek Trump Princess, the 
world's longest private yacht, and will upgrade to an even bigger flagship. 
</P>
<P>
"We've had quite a lot of inquiries," said a spokesman for London yacht agents 
Nigel Burgess, which is charged with selling the Princess. 
</P>
<P>
An advertisement in the Financial Times described the 282-foot Trump Princess 
as "the world's most spectacular motor yacht . . . considered by all to be the 
greatest yacht ever built." 
</P>
<P>
Trump, 43, bought his Princess, built as Nabila for indicted Saudi arms dealer 
Adnan Khashoggi, from the Sultan of Brunei in 1987 for what he called a "song" 
-- a mere $30 million. 
</P>
<P>
Trump's new craft, being built by Amels Holland shipyard for delivery in 1992, 
will be 420 feet, or 10 feet longer than Britain's royal yacht Britannia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
