The magazine also has a "good men who went bad" category for Elvis Presley, 
Marlon Brando, Bryant Gumbel, Jim Bakker, Jackie Mason, Dan Rather, Bill Cosby 
and David Letterman and a "good men who stayed good" class for Paul Newman, 
Woody Allen, Robert Redford, Gregory Peck, Walter Cronkite, George Burns, Sean 
Connery, Mikhail Baryshnikov. 
